Udeh Okoye, the National Youth Leader of the opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), was on Monday abducted on his farm in Enugu State. According to Ebere Amaraizu, the spokesperson for the Enugu Stae Police Command, Okoye was allegedly held at gunpoint and taken away by his assailants. He said: “We are on it, but because of the nature of the incident, we would not be able to disclose many details. He went to his farm and was kidnapped, that should do for now.”